      "content": "# GET /user Endpoint Documentation\n\n## 1. Overview and Purpose\nThis section details the primary function of the `/user` endpoint.\n\n### 1.1 Core Functionality\nThe endpoint is designed to fetch the complete profile information for the currently authenticated user.\n\n## 2. Request Details\n### 2.1 HTTP Method and Path\nIt utilizes the `GET` method against the `/user` resource path.\n\n## 3. Response Structure\n### 3.1 Successful Response (200 OK)\nThe successful response body contains the user's profile data.\n\n#### 3.1.1 Data Fields\n*   **ID**: Unique identifier for the user.\n*   **Name**: The user's full display name.\n*   **Email**: The primary contact email address.\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n### 4.1 Common Status Codes\nDetails on expected error responses, such as 401 Unauthorized.",
